content.text: JavaScript Sets
A JavaScript Set is a collection of unique values.
content.html: A JavaScript Set is a collection of unique values.

content.text: Each value can only occur once in a Set.
content.html: Each value can only occur once in a Set.

content.text: The values can be of any type, primitive values or objects.
content.html: The values can be of any type, primitive values or objects.

content.text: Create a Set and add values:

content.code_html:
// Create a Set
 const letters = new Set();

// Add Values to the Set
 letters.add("a");
letters.add("b");
letters.add("c");

content.text: Create a Set and add variables:

content.code_html:
// Create a Set
 const letters = new Set();

// Create Variables
 const a = "a";
const b = "b";
const c = "c";

// Add Variables to the Set
 letters.add(a);
letters.add(b);
letters.add(c);

content.text: The add() Method

content.code_html:
letters.add("d");
letters.add("e");

content.text: If you add equal elements, only the first will be saved:

content.text: Listing the Elements
You can list all Set elements (values) with a for..of loop:
content.html: You can list all Set elements (values) with a for..of loop:

content.code_html:
// Create a Set
 const letters = new Set(["a","b","c"]);

// List all Elements
 let text = "";
for (const x of letters) {
  text += x;
}

content.text: Browser Support
Set is an ES6 feature (JavaScript 2015).
ES6 is fully supported in all modern browsers since June 2017:

May 2016 Apr 2017 Jun 2017 Sep 2016 Jun 2016
